"Teng H., Yamasaki A.","Dissolution of buoyant CO2 drops in a counterflow water tunnel simulating the deep ocean waters",2000,"Energy Conversion and Management","41","9",,"929","937",,,10.1016/S0196-8904(99)00145-4,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0033894534&partnerID=40&md5=fb16a3f6cff182c4eba02815ee78e0e9","Natl. Inst. of Mat. and Chem. Res., 1-1 Higashi, Tsukuba, 305, Ibaraki, Japan","Teng, H., Natl. Inst. of Mat. and Chem. Res., 1-1 Higashi, Tsukuba, 305, Ibaraki, Japan; Yamasaki, A., Natl. Inst. of Mat. and Chem. Res., 1-1 Higashi, Tsukuba, 305, Ibaraki, Japan","We investigated the dissolution of CO2 drops in a high pressure counterflow water tunnel simulating ocean conditions down to 2000 m below the ocean surface. In comparison of the behavior of the buoyant CO2 drops observed in our experiments with that reported previously for motionless CO2 drops in seawater or water, the following significant differences are noticed: (1) the CO2 drops in buoyant motion dissolve much faster than the motionless CO2 drops and (2) hydrate does not always form on the buoyant CO2 drops, as it was reported in the literature to be an unavoidable phenomenon on the motionless drops. This suggests that buoyant motion influences the physical and chemical behavior of the CO2 drops in seawater dramatically.",,"Air pollution control; Buoyancy; Carbon dioxide; Dissolution; Flow of water; Global warming; High pressure effects; Mass transfer; Seawater; Water tunnel; Ocean dumping",,,,,,"Handa, N., Ohsumi, T., (1995) Direct Ocean Disposal of Carbon Dioxide, , Tokyo: Terra Scientific Publishing Company; Teng, H., Yamasaki, A., Shindo, Y., (1996) Energy, 21, p. 765; Teng, H., Yamasaki, A., (1997) Energy, 22, p. 751; Aya, I., Yamane, K., Yamada, N., (1993) CO2 Fixation and Efficient Utilization of Energy, p. 351. , Y. et al. Tamaura. Tokyo: Tokyo Institute of Technology; Aya, I., Yamane, K., Yamada, N., (1992) Fundamentals of Phase Change: Freezing, Melting, and Sublimation, p. 17. , P.G. Kroeger, & Y. Bayazitoglu. New York: ASME; Fujioka, Y., Takeuchi, K., Shindo, Y., Komiyama, H., (1994) Int. J. Energy Research, 18, p. 765; Shindo, Y., Fujioka, Y., Takeuchi, K., Komiyama, H., (1995) Int. J. Chem. Kinet., 27, p. 569; Winnikow, S., Chao, B.T., (1966) Physics of Fluids, 9, p. 50; Lode, T., Heideger, W.J., (1970) Chem. Eng. Sci., 25, p. 1081; Davidson, J.F., Kirk, F.A., (1969) Chem. Eng. Sci., 24, p. 1529; Moo-Young, M., Fulford, G., Cheyne, I., (1971) Ind. Eng. Chem. Fundam., 10, p. 157; Maini, B.B., Bishnoi, P.R., (1981) Chem. Eng. Sci., 36, p. 183; Teng, H., Yamasaki, A., (1998) J. Chem. Eng. Data, 43, p. 2; Vukalovich, M.P., Altunin, V.V., (1968) Thermodynamical Properties of Carbon Dioxide, , London: Collet's; Millero, F.J., Sohn, M.L., (1992) Chemical Oceanography, , Florida: CRC Press; Teng, H., Yamasaki, A., (1998) Int. J. Heat & Mass Transfer, 41, p. 4315","Teng, H.; Natl Inst of Materials and Chemical, Research, Ibaraki, Japan",,,"Elsevier Science Ltd, Exeter, United Kingdom",,,,,01968904,,ECMAD,,"English","Energy Convers. Manage.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-0033894534
